NAME

    Data::Password::Top10000 - Check if a given string is in the Top 10000
    list of common passwords

VERSION

    version 1.0.1

SYNOPSIS

        use v5.24;
        use Data::Password::Top10000 (is_in_top10000);
    
        my $password = '12345';
        if ( is_in_top10000( $password ) ) {
            say 'please use an other password';
        }

DESCRIPTION

    At https://github.com/danielmiessler/SecLists a "security tester's
    companion" is curated. Part of this companion is a list of the Top
    10000 used passwords. It is good practice to disallow users to use
    those passwords.

FUNCTIONS

 is_in_top10000

    Checks

